history.content: Took EE105 with Nguyen. It was a great class. There are weekly problem sets that usually take about 5-6 hours a week. Weekly lab + lab reports, usually 3-4 hours for the first few. He had 2 projects (labs 5 and 6) during the last five or so weeks of the semester. Lab 5 is not bad and probably took like 10 hours, but lab 6 took near 45-50 hours. Overall workload of the class is definitely quite a step up from EE16AB, but doable. I don't know exactly how much work 61C is with Garcia, but I probably wouldn't take anymore project-based classes along with these two. -- Just a side note: if you're focusing more on CS and don't see yourself doing much EE, I wouldn't really recommend taking 105 and the more CS-inclined people I knew in the class ended up regretting it, but that's just my opinion/observation. 105 is more of an analog class, so if you're more focused on CS and want to know some more EE, I would recommend EECS151.
